metadata.name: sinuosity #244
metadata.description:
sinuosity is defined as:

- (n.) the ability to curve or bend easily and flexibly.

sinuous is defined as a couple of things:

- (adj.) having many curves and turns.
- (adj.) lithe and supple.

each curve anchors to the center. 

maybe that center is a life. (maybe that center is you.)

maybe that curve is a relationship. (or a job.) (or repressed trauma that needs processing.)

maybe that curve has other curves within. (it probably does.)

sometimes there are many curves at once. (usually this the case.) 

occasionally, there may only be one. (life isn‚Äôt always so complicated.) 

whatever curves the moment contains it can help to step away and see how they come together. (this is not always easy.)

metadata.name: Ceremony #354
metadata.description:
This series celebrates fxhash turning one. #fxhashturnsone

I‚Äôm so grateful for this place and have ho idea how to adequately articulate how much this platform has changed my life, but it has. A million thanks to the team. You are so appreciated as are the artists and collectors that have made this such a beautiful community. ü•Ç

Definitely check out ‚ÄúForever‚Äù mode by tapping ‚ÄúF‚Äù or mouse click/tap ‚Äî it will animate (you guessed it) forever and will change its layout every 365 frames, in honor of this wonderful year, and every year after. Some forever modes will ‚Äúnever forget‚Äù and others will fade as they progress. No idea if that‚Äôs a metaphor but it is a trait, that much I know.

All primary sales are donated to Code/Art, which is a charity that uses ‚Äú‚Ä¶Art to Inspire Girls in Computer Science.‚Äù Read about Code/Art here: https://www.code-art.com/

Ceremony uses public domain art (which is the original, more implicit version CC0) made exclusively by women.

See fxtext article linked from the project page for a gallery of the source material and other notes.

Ceremony is also CC0, so feel free use anything here in other projects.

You can read more about CC0 here:
https://creativecommons.org/share-your-work/public-domain/cc0/

F : ‚ÄúForever‚Äù mode (tap after initial render completes)
P : Pause/Play
(mouse click/tap also works to start ‚ÄúForever‚Äù mode or Pause/Play)

A : Add Grain (only works when paused in ‚ÄúForever‚Äù mode.)
G : Toggle Grain (resets the whole piece)
M : Toggle Matte (resets the whole piece)

S : Save Image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density (resets the whole piece)
(Default pixel density is 1 @ 2000x2000)

If you want to start in "Forever" mode, you can append "&forever=true" to the url in the live view.
You can also add pixel density to the url by appending ‚Äú&density=2‚Äù (or 3, 4, etc) to have it render at higher resolutions by default.

metadata.name: Elements of Truth #29
metadata.description:
A broken mirror is a representation of the fragmented and incomplete nature of truth, with each piece of the mirror representing a different aspect or perspective on a given issue. Just as a broken mirror can only show a distorted and incomplete reflection of reality, our understanding of truth can also be incomplete and limited by our individual experiences and perspectives.
A broken mirror conveys the idea of reflection and self-awareness inviting us to reveal some aspect of the truth or to provide a glimpse into a deeper understanding of reality. Why might even spot o stylised representation of ourselves in one of the fragments.

- hit 'p' so save .png
- hit 's' to save .svg

metadata.name: Syzers #298
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

¬∑¬∑¬∑¬∑ On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ¬∑¬∑¬∑¬∑

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template. 
"FXHASH PFP Token Generator" https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

for best resolution "open live" then use the "download image" button on the lower right corner ;)

metadata.description:
Hand-scrawled documentation of abstract structures. A journal from another realm.

Press 's' to save an image while in full-screen mode.

If you want to increase the resolution of the saved image, add e.g. &size=2000 after the live/fullscreen view URL to render the canvas at that specific pixel width (default = browser sized). metadata.name: The Spectrum Of Nature #51
metadata.description:
*\_../*`¬¨-‚Äô\/*`¬¨‚Äô‚Äô¬¨`*\/‚Äô-¬¨`*\.._/*

Nature, nature, evolving might‚Ä¶ Silent inventor, always right.
Where is the edge of nature and where do we begin?  
What is of nature and what is of man? 
Isn't everything made by nature's hands?

To know more about the concept and technicalities of this piece, see the fxtext article ‚ÄúThe spectrum of nature - a short making of‚Äù. Link at the bottom. If you‚Äôd rather just ignore my personal meaning, feel free to skip the article. 

\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\

Basic info:
The piece comes in possible portrait or landscape versions. Both have a relative size of 1 by 1.5. So the initial render will be 1000px wide and 1500px high for portrait. And 1500x1000 for landscape. With the ability to scale this up (see below).

The piece uses WebGL, so will perform much better with a graphics card. A faster computer will obviously be better, though I've done my very best to make it fast and efficient for any old laptop. My hope is that you will find the render process quick and enjoyable for the amount of detail that‚Äôs present. 

../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\..

Controls:
Press the [s] key to save the initial render. You will need to wait a few seconds after all the elements have stopped loading. A box will pop up in the top left saying ‚Äúdone‚Äù for 4 seconds when it‚Äôs ready. For the [s] key to work you may need to open in a new tab. But can right click save otherwise.

Larger sizes:
Press the [2-9] keys to save a resolution of that key size. So [2] saves a 2000x3000 size image, [9] saves a 9000x13500 size image etc. Unless you are making some very large prints you probably won‚Äôt need more than 4k (even 2-3k is big). Though the option is there. 

There may be slight variations in the textures for the larger renders, this is because the shader code has to redraw the textures at the higher pixel resolution, and getting the textures where they sit is more of an art than a science. All the elements remain exact however. 

/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*

Made with javascript and some small extra code:
A palette creator by @nathansonic
Noisejs - github.com/josephg/noisejs - Perlin noise generator
Twgl - github.com/greggman/twgl.js - A small webGL helper.
